div1.p: Taken by force, and unlawfully without the jurisdiction of this court and without the Territory of Washington.

Whenfore your petition pray that a writ of habeas corpus may be granted. Directed to the RaidJC Mitchell + John H McGraw commanding him to liave the body of your petitioner before your honor at a time and place therin to be apealead to do and mean what shall then and there be considered by your honor concerning. Together with the time and cause of your petitioners detention, and said writ, and that he may be returned to his liberty George W H Carson

Territory of Washington County of King ss: George W. Anderson, being first duly herrin, according to land, when his oath dryers and says: that he is the petitioner named in the pregiven petition, that he has said the name. Knows the contents itnersg?? and believes the name to be true. George H. Anderson
Sworn and subscribed before me this 1st Day of October A.D. 1889, Thomas R. Hardin Notary Public in and for King County Washington Territory.
